cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of millimeter-wave (mmWave) communications for wireless personal area networks (WPANs), which falls under the category of networked and internet-connected systems (cs.NI). The paper also focuses on beamforming and spatial reuse, which are techniques commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a scheduling scheme and formulates it as a mixed-integer linear program (MILP), which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
